        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. Evening</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sanderson</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have seen Sir John. He thinks L. Playfair w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be the best man to present the petition, as he attends to medical subjects; but if Playfair objects on any grounds he will present it.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> He doubts about wisdom of any petition.— I showed him our bill &amp; he thought this a far more important &amp; useful proceeding, &amp; suggested an alteration in <hi rend="underline">Title</hi> &amp; <hi rend="underline">Preamble</hi>, giving it a more humanitarian aspect, &amp; he thought this not a little important.— I have written to Litchfield &amp; told him Sir John’s suggestion.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>Sir J. thinks it w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be better that petition sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be presented to both Houses of Parliament.—</p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p>
<p>Will you ask L. Playfair?</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 Playfair] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘he’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.3 He … petition.—] <hi rend="italic">inserted</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.5 more] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n4">1.6 have] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘sh’ </note>
            </div>

           
            
